Class Triple

  • java.lang.Object
    • Triple
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Hex, java.io.Serializable

    public class Triple
extends java.lang.Object
implements Hex, java.io.Serializable
    Three Yarns that all intesect each other. Any one of these Yarns intersects the other two consecutively, with no other Yarn intersections (Joins) between. This corresponds to a trio of rhombs, all of which share a common point and any two of which share a common edge. The union of three such rhombs is a hexagon, and that hexagon can be flipped by reversing the order of all pairs of Yarn intersections. We do not check for these properties on construction; we merely assume that they are satisfied.
